## Definite First-Pass Conclusion

& [Conclusion_001] is definite_for_current_scope
  + [statement] is the special-prime families tested so far are useful probes and sampling surfaces, but they are not sufficient explanatory variables for whole-field theta or psi interval movement
  + [reason] is interval family increments do not align simply with theta or psi movement signs in the saved finite trace
  + [next_boundary] is further work should either add prime-power decomposition or add a zeta-adjacent family such as irregular primes, not strengthen claims from the current family set
